Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-only tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
// Or if using MSTest 3.x+:
[SupportedOSPlatform("windows")]
// Simplest built-in approach:
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
        return;
    }
    // test logic
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI - requires local GPU");
        return;
    }
    // test logic
}
```

Then exclude by category in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky external API — retry with `[Timeout]` and conditional ignore

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Timeout(10000)] // fail fast on timeout
[RetryFailedTest(3)] // MSTest 3.x+ built-in retry
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    // test logic that calls external API
}
```

If on older MSTest without `[RetryFailedTest]`, use a manual loop:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void WeatherApiTest_WithRetry()
{
    const int maxRetries = 3;
    Exception? last = null;

    for (int i = 0; i < maxRetries; i++)
    {
        try
        {
            // call weather API and assert
            return; // success
        }
        catch (Exception ex) { last = ex; }
    }
    Assert.Fail($"Failed after {maxRetries} attempts: {last?.Message}");
}
```

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string? _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (_tempFile is not null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
        // assertions that might fail — cleanup still runs
    }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**
| Scenario | Recommended approach |
|----------|---------------------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or `--filter` |
| Skip in CI | Environment variable check + `[TestCategory]` filter |
| Flaky/retry | `[RetryFailedTest(n)]` (MSTest 3.x+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` attribute on a method |
